  <T n="name">0x7F0DB6CE<!--Welcome to Chestnut Ridge--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_WelcomeToChestnutRidge_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:282586d4c3abb21b</T>
      <T n="text">0xEB91BE13<!--With so many things to do in Chestnut Ridge, it helps to have one spot with all the information you need!\n\nEach neighborhood has a <b>Ranch Community Board</b> where you can<ul><li>learn about the town and its residents</li><li>purchase Ranch Animals</li><li>hire a Ranch Hand to help you with your Ranch</li><li>pick up odd jobs around town</li><li>send your Horse to train and compete at the Equestrian Center</li></ul>If you want a Community Board of your own for ultra convenient access, purchase one from the <b>Outdoor Activities</b> category in <b>Build Mode</b> and place it on your home lot!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_WelcomeToChestnutRidge_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:282586d4c3abb218</T>
      <T n="text">0x823E308A<!--<b>Hay Now! Equestrian Center</b> in <b>New Appaloosa</b> is the premier location for everything related to Horses. Train up your trusty steed and test your Horse's Skills in five types of competitions: <b>Barrel Racing</b>, <b>Endurance Racing</b>, <b>Show Jumping</b>, <b>Western Pleasure</b>, or compete with the best of the best in the <b>Ultimate Horse Championship</b>.\n\nThe Equestrian Center is open from 7 AM to 7 PM every day.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_WelcomeToChestnutRidge_Slide3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:282586d4c3abb219</T>
      <T n="text">0xD3737E95<!--Preparing for a competition at the Hay Now! Equestrian Center? <b>Duke's Hall</b> can meet all the essential Horse Care needs so you and your steed can be in top form.\n\n<b>New Appaloosa</b> also is the hot spot for all the Ranchers and Nectar Makers when they finish a hard day's work.\n\nHead to <b>The Rusty Horseshoe</b> for a time of boisterous country dancing. Take a seat and savor a sip of Nectar at <b>The Oak Barrel</b>.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_WelcomeToChestnutRidge_Slide4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:282586d4c3abb21e</T>
      <T n="text">0xD487207C<!--While in <b>New Appaloosa</b>, you can pick up supplies from <b>Bits & Bales Mercantile</b>, which has rotating inventory plus Nectar Making ingredients and even Mini Goats and Mini Sheep.\n\nAt <b>Chestnut Chaps</b>, Sims can plan and change outfits to gussy up and ensure they look their best for their time in town.\n\nOutside of town for adventurous souls, <b>Galloping Gulch</b> is said to be home to the ominous <b>Dreadhorse Caverns</b>. Find it to discover what the mysterious cave contains....--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP14\UI\Lessons\EP14_WelcomeToChestnutRidge_Slide5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:282586d4c3abb21f</T>
      <T n="text">0x50503222<!--Your ranch is an important part of this Chestnut Ridge, too! Establish your presence by <b>naming your ranch</b> and <b>decorating your Ranch Sign</b>.\n\nYou can find these large entrance signs in <b>Build Mode</b> by searching for "<b>Ranch Sign</b>". They have a <i>ton</i> of spots to hang decorations such as metal animal signage (text search for "<b>signage</b>") and a variety of <b>Wall Decorations</b>. Experiment to find your own brand of ranch flair!\n\nEarn more signage by achieving the highest levels of a Sim's <b>Horse Riding Skill</b> and the Horse's four Skills: <b>Temperament, Agility, Jumping, and Endurance</b>!\n\nOnce you have a Sign, select it to name your ranch. Happy ranching!--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
